<HEADLINE> Stock Market in Shanghai Fluctuates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Under the influence of stock
bourses of neighboring countries, Shanghai Stock Exchange recorded
an up-and-down operation this week with the transaction volume slightly
higher than the previous week.
</P>
<P>
The market opened high at the beginning of the week and soared
to 1,400 points on Wednesday. However, it dived to 1,382 points on
Thursday, 0.52 percent lower than the previous week and reported
no rebound today.
</P>
<P>
The B-share -- stocks issued to overseas investors -- closed at
41.48 points today, 4.75 points down from the last week. Of the 52
B-shares, 38 declined. The transaction volume of B share for this
week totaled 85 million yuan, down by 38 percent.
</P>
<P>
China's fourth investment fund, Anxin, was listed on the
Shanghai Stock Exchange today. It opened at a price of 1.68 yuan
per unit and closed at 1.64 yuan with a daily transaction volume
of 510 million yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
