<HEADLINE> Swaziland to Build 20 Dams </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Swaziland has begun building
20 dams in drought-prone parts of the country at a cost of about
3 million U.S. Dollars, the Agriculture Ministry said Friday.
</P>
<P>
About half of the cost, or 1.5 million Dollars, has been
allocated by the European Union and the Swazi government will
provide the rest, South African Press Association quoted the
ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
The dams would provide irrigation for cultivating undeveloped
rural areas in the tiny mountain kingdom, and supply water for
human consumption and livestock. The dams would also be stocked
with fish.
</P>
<P>
The two-year dam project would provide badly needed job
opportunities for Swazis and meanwhile benefit Swazi-owned
construction companies, the ministry said.  
</P>
