<HEADLINE> Three American Players To Be Fined </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- American coach Steve Sampson said
three of players who publicly crticised him during the World Cup
would be fined.
</P>
<P>
Sampson has promised the fines would be "significant" and that
he would not pick any of the players concerned if he retains his job.
</P>
<P>
Alexei Lalas, Tab Ramos and Jeff Agoos have all said they would
refuse to play under Sampson.
</P>
<P>
The American team lost all their three group matches and
Sampson's future as coach will be determined within the next month
by the United States Soccer Federation.
</P>
<P>
"I don't think any level of unprofessionalism is acceptable,"
said Sampson,"It's unfortunate they feel so free to voice their
opinions about me when I have given them so much respect and credit."
</P>
<P>
Sampson rejected the suggestion he might resign:"I've worked too
hard and I'm not going to let one or two individuals dictate my career."
</P>
<P>
Sampson would not reveal the exact size of fines to the
players:"Those concerned will be notified by letter over the next
few days." Sampson said. 
</P>
