<HEADLINE> Malawi Ready to Assist Any Probe into Machel's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Malawian government has said
it will cooperate in any efforts intended to determine the cause
of the death of late Samora Machel, former president of
Mozambique, and those who may have contributed to it.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed in a press document from the office of the
Ministry of Justice and Attorney General, following revelations
that the Samora Machel was assassinated and not killed in a plane
crash, the Malawi News Agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
"The Malawian government wishes to assure the government of
Mozambique, the South Africa's Truth and Reconciliation
Commission (TRC) any lawful authority set up for the purpose of
investigating the circumstances surrounding the death of late
president Machel," said the statement.
</P>
<P>
The Democratic Malawi will not shield any person in the former
regime of the Malawi Congress Party (MCP) government who may have
taken part, directly or indirectly, in the untimely demise of the
late president, it added.
</P>
<P>
Graca Machel, the widow of the late president, spilled the
beans last Tuesday in her lengthy testimony to the Truth and
Reconciliation Commission. 
</P>
