<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Asks W.African Countries to Mediate Bissau </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- France has asked the Economic
Community of West African States (CEDEAO) to mediate between the
fighting sides of Guinea-Bissau, said French officials Friday.
</P>
<P>
Insurgent soldiers of Guinea-Bissau have been fighting the
forces loyal to President Joao Bernardo Vieira, supported by
Senegal and Guinea-Conakry, since June 7.
</P>
<P>
Paris is also contacting the president of the Organization of
African Unity, Burkina Faso President Blaise Compaore, to seek
support from the pan-African organization for mediation by the
CEDEAO.
</P>
<P>
The CEDEAO, presently chaired by Nigeria, will hold a meeting
Monday in Abidjan, Cote d'Ivoire, to discuss the situation in
Guinea-Bissau.
</P>
<P>
France says that it will get involved in the conflict in
Bissau, because of its new Africa policy of non-interference.
</P>
