<HEADLINE> World Bank Loan to Finance Kazakhstan's Pension Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved here
Thursday a loan of 300 million U.S. dollar to help finance
Kazakhstan's pension reform.
</P>
<P>
The loan is earmarked for the Kazakhstan Pension Reform
Adjustment Project designed to switch the country's existing
pension system over to a fully-funded one.
</P>
<P>
It is expected to help with macroeconomic stability and
restructuring, social protection and public information,
government management and operation in the reform process.
</P>
<P>
In addition, legal and regulatory framework, as well as related
institutions are also areas targeted for receiving the funding.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank loan would make up part of the fiscal deficit
brought about by the reform, which is equivalent to some 1.7
percent of Kazakhstan's gross domestic product (GDP). 
</P>
