<HEADLINE> IPE Introduces Daily Natural Gas Futures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- From Friday, 26 June Daily
contracts for Natural Gas Futures are available from the
International Petroleum Exchange (IPE), reflecting demand from the
industry for a shorter term hedging tool.
</P>
<P>
The IPE announced that these Dailies include a contract for the
next day, as well as the following six days. This means that
companies will be able to hedge using individual days for the week
ahead.
</P>
<P>
Companies are already able to trade in monthly strips for daily
deliveries up to a maximum of 15 months, and for daily deliveries
for the balance of the current month.
</P>
<P>
As for the existing contracts, the minimum trading size for
Dailies will be 5 lots at 1,000 therms a lot. The contract is
denominated in sterling with the minimum tick size unchanged at
0.01p/therm.
</P>
<P>
Natural Gas futures were launched by the IPE on 31 January
1997. The contract has already developed into a key indicator of
price trends in the UK market.
</P>
<P>
At the beginning of April the contract was extended to 15
forward months from 12 previously as a result of demand from the
users. 
</P>
</TEXT>
