<HEADLINE> Kenya's Foreign Policy to Maintain Regional </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Kenya's foreign policy is to
"attain and maintain regional stability in eastern Africa with a
view to Promoting her economic interests in the region," Foreign
Minister Bonaya Godana said Friday evening.
</P>
<P>
Speaking while launching the first issue of the monthly
Foreign Affairs Bulletin here, Godana said Kenya's foreign policy
is about advancing interests of Kenya and Kenyans.
</P>
<P>
"Our core national interests comprise safeguarding our
territorial integrity and sovereignty and promotion of economic
and commercial interests," said the honorable minister, who
assumed the post since Kanu won the general election last
December.
</P>
<P>
Godana stressed, "We have emphasized peaceful co-existence,
respect for national sovereignty and territorial integrity of
other states and adherence to the charters of the Organization of
African Unity and the United Nations."
</P>
<P>
Addressing about a hundred foreign diplomats, reporters and
officials at a cocktail here, the minister admitted that Kenya
seeks a pro-active role in regional international ties, saying
that conflict prevention, management and resolution "remain a
central plank of our foreign policy."
</P>
<P>
Kenya has been mediating on the Sudanese conflict and
appealing for a cease-fire in southern Sudan as it is the
president of the seven-member Intergovernmental Authority on
Development (IGAD).
</P>
<P>
"Kenya supports peaceful resolution of conflicts and disputes
through negotiations and mediation as opposed to the use of force
and remains active in initiating peaceful negotiations in the
Great Lakes region and the Horn of Africa," Godana said,
referring to the Burundi peace talks and the recent conflict
between Ethiopia and Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
Kenya would like to "see North-South economic equities and
believes in the South-South cooperation," he noted, adding that
"we are determined to support the efforts of the Group of 77
toward economic development." 
</P>
</TEXT>
