<DOCNO> XIE19980627.0053 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Launch Polio Eradication Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania will launch a
polio eradication campaign in the second half of the year, a
mobilization committee secretary, Magreth Fimbo, said here
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The first round of immunization will take place on August 1
and 2 and its second round will be on September 12 and 13, Fimbo
said.
</P>
<P>
Sixty percent of polio vaccines have arrived in the country
and are being distributed in various regions. The vaccines are
11.26 million doses from Japan, she said.
</P>
<P>
The remaining 40 percent will arrive next month, the official
added.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the vaccines, equipment for immunization are
forthcoming and every region has its plans to make the
immunization of children under five years successful, she said.
</P>
<P>
"To make the immunization campaign successful, senior health
officials have been gone to different regions to make sure that
there are proper arrangement for it," Fimbo said.
</P>
<P>
She added that vaccinators and health attendants in regions
with poor records in past years' immunization campaigns are under
training so that the regions can perform well in this year's
campaign.
</P>
<P>
The official named the regions as Mbeya, Rukwa, Mara, Arusha,
Coast, Tabora and Dar es Salaam.
</P>
<P>
Fimbo said that the educators will also give services in the
regions of Mtwara, Dodoma, Morogoro, Tanga, Ruvuma, Shinyanga and
Singida after receiving funds from UNICEF.
</P>
<P>
The national immunization against polio for children under
five started in 1996. 
</P>
