<HEADLINE> Shanghai Establishes Securities Advisory Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, the economic and
financial center of China, today established a legal affairs
advisory group to serve local securities firms.
</P>
<P>
The group was formed under the sponsorship of the Shanghai
Securities Industry Association and was jointly founded by the
local public security bureau, procuratorate and judicial
departments, as well as established law offices.
</P>
<P>
The advisors will consult with securities firms in wide-ranging
areas, including issues pertinent to law, regulations and
policies. It will also help firms train employees, administer
relations between financial, securities, taxation and business
administration departments, and fulfill the requirements of
organizations such as the Securities Association and Shanghai
Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
The advisory group will also assist securities firms in
handling relations with both competitors and shareholders.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yuchun, chairman of the Shenyin-Wanguo Securities
Co. Ltd, noted the necessity for establishing the advisory group.
</P>
<P>
"Unethical practices on the the part of securities firms and
economic disputes between related firms and investors have
occurred frequently in recent years. The advisory group will help
to effectively solve problems," according to Wang.
</P>
<P>
Experts note that the market is expanding and becoming
increasingly complicated. However, they point out that the
advisory group will help safeguard fair competition in the
marketplace and facilitate the growth of Shanghai's stock market.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
