<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Justice Minister Calls for Rule of Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Justice Minister Gao
Chgangli today called for judicial departments to fulfill their
role and implement the plan based on the rule of law.
</P>
<P>
The general plan covering "the rule of law and building a
socialist country governed by laws" presented by General Secretary
Jiang Zemin during the 15th National Congress of the Communist
Party of China summarized the historical experience of the Party
and a general outline of efforts to establish democracy and the
legal system over the 20 years since the introduction of reform
and opening," according to Gao. The minister made the comments at
the final meeting of judges from across the nation.
</P>
<P>
"We should strictly follow this plan of raising the level of
judicial work to new heights," said the minister.
</P>
<P>
Gao said that legal services, education and research, as well
as various other areas, should be included in the priority tasks of
the Party.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that legal services must be expanded along with the
development of the socialist market economy, and noted that the
spread of law and administration under the guidance of the legal
system represent concrete practices of the rule of law.
</P>
<P>
"Administration in accordance with law is the path that we must
follow in order to ensure the full realization of the rule of
law," according to the minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
