<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Cup Expects First Ever "Golden Ball" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The second round competitions of
World Cup finals will begin on Saturday afternoon with a major
innovation at the finals -- the "golden goal" rule.
</P>
<P>
The knock-out stage will adopt the sudden-death "golden goal"
rule for the first time in World Cup history.
</P>
<P>
Under the new rule, if two teams play to a draw after 90 minutes
regulation time, two 15-minute periods of extra-time will be played as
usual. But the game stops immediatly when one team scores in
extra-time.
</P>
<P>
FIFA first introduced the rule at the 1993 world youth
championships in Australia and has since extended it to the Olympics
and the Confederations Cup. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
