<HEADLINE> Beijing Customs Department Seizes Psychotropic Substances </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Customs officers at Beijing's
Capital International Airport have solved six cases involving
the illegal trafficking of psychotropic substances so far this
year.
</P>
<P>
The most recent case occurred on June 24 when customs officers
confiscated 8,000 tabs of amfepiamone, a psychotropic substance
classified by the United Nations, in the luggage of two tourists
from the Republic of Korea preparing to return home.
</P>
<P>
Customs officers confiscated over 12,000 tablets of amfepiamone
in earlier luggage inspections, with a total of 24,000 amfepiamone
tabs confiscated in the five previous cases.
</P>
<P>
Amfepiamone is a strictly controlled substance and Chinese drug
stores are prohibited from selling the product. 
</P>
