<HEADLINE> Celebrations Begin as First Anniversary Approaches in HKSAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 27 (Xinhua) -- People took to the streets in
showers to join all kinds of activities over the weekend to
celebrate the approaching first anniversary of the establishment
of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) of China.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa and Administrative Secretary
Anson Chan were among the SAR officials to appear at a carnival in
Kowloon Park Saturday afternoon.
</P>
