Kong Branch and the Commissioner's Office of the Chinese Foreign
Ministry to officiate a flag-flying ceremony at the end of the
Kowloon Peninsular opposite to the Hong Kong island.
</P>
<P>
From this Saturday to July 12, China's national flags and the
SAR flags will be flown over the posts of street lights along the
eight-kilometer streets in downtown Kowloon.
</P>
<P>
An organizer of the activity said the flag-flying is aimed at
creating a festive atmosphere and displaying a new look to the
city as well as helping publicize the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
In the following week, similar carnivals, song and dance
performances, exhibitions, athletic events, and seminars will be
held in different places throughout the SAR to celebrate the first
anniversary.
</P>
<P>
A grand celebration organized by the SAR government is
scheduled for July 1. Chinese President Jiang Zemin will be
attending the celebration. 
</P>
