<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Feature: Hong Kong - One of Safest Cities in World (2) By Feng Xiuju </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Operations mounted locally and internationally have been
successful in preventing the large scale importation of illicit
drugs, particularly heroin, methyl amphetamine and ecstasy.
</P>
<P>
"Our long standing relationships with key overseas law
enforcement agencies have been crucial in ensuring that we play an
important role in the international fight against drugs," Ng said.
</P>
<P>
He also noted the 17 percent reduction in triad related crime
in 1997, saying that the successful confiscation of criminal
assets at the end of 1997 stood at 261 million Hong Kong dollars
(33.46 million U.S. dollars), with a further 244 million Hong Kong
dollars (31.28 million U.S. dollars) either frozen or pending
confiscation.
</P>
<P>
Coordination with the mainland's Public Security Bureau and
international law enforcement agencies has successfully reduced
organized vehicle thefts and smuggling by 18.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the commissioner of police received a total of 2,939
complaints against the Police Force from the public last year,
showing a decrease of 370 cases compared with 1996.
</P>
<P>
Corruption complaints against police officers decreased by 12.5
percent from 576 in 1996 to 512 in 1997, he added.
</P>
<P>
Ng stressed that after Hong Kong returned to China on July 1
last year, "we continue to enforce the law in exactly the same way
as before."
</P>
<P>
The concern that police officers in senior ranks would leave
the service prior to the transfer of the power has proven to be
unfounded, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The vast majority of expatriate officers remained committed to
Hong Kong and the Police Force, with 402 remaining in the Force at
the end of 1997," he said.
</P>
<P>
A recent public opinion survey shows that the overall majority
of respondents, about 80 percent, felt a strong sense of safety
living in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
So, Hong Kong remains one of the safest and most stable
societies in the world.
</P>
<P>
Ng attributed the present good order in Hong Kong's society
mainly to the joint efforts of the Hong Kong Police and other
government departments, as well as their close cooperation with the
relevant mainland security departments.
</P>
<P>
In order to ensure Hong Kong's safety, more security staff
members are sent out on patrol duty everyday in streets.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the security equipment has been improved further.
</P>
<P>
One of the most important factors in this regard is, of course,
related to Hong Kong's return to China, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
