<HEADLINE> Chinese Companies Join Motorola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 27 ( Xinhua) -- The Guangzhou Jinpeng Group
Co. Ltd., Jingpeng Electronic Information Machinery Co. Ltd. and
Motorola China Electronics Co. Ltd. reached Thursday a framework
agreement calling for the establishment of a cooperative mobile
telecommunications venture in Guangzhou, capital of Guangdong
Province.
</P>
<P>
The agreement calls for the venture to design, develop, market
and offer after-sales services for GSM mobile telecommunication
systems software.
</P>
<P>
The agreement stipulates that Jingpeng will provide related
technology, while Motorola will assume responsibility for planning
and management training.
</P>
<P>
China's mobile telecommunications system continues to develop
rapidly, with some 10 million new users added on an annual
basis. Mobile telecommunication is rapidly emerging as a pillar of
the telecommunications sector.  
</P>
