<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania Records 15 Plane Accidents in 1995-97 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania has witnessed 15
plane accidents between 1995 and 1997, according to Tanzanian
Deputy Minister for Communications and Transport Maua Daftari.
</P>
<P>
These accidents occurred because of bad weather, recklessness
of the pilots and mechanical failures, the Guardian Saturday
newspaper quoted Daftari as saying.
</P>
<P>
The deputy minister revealed the figure Thursday at the
National Assembly session in Dodoma when answering questions
raised by members of parliament on the record of the country's
plane accidents and causes during 1995-1997.
</P>
<P>
Daftari denied claims that passenger planes were not properly
checked before take-off, saying that there were thorough
examinations before any planes registered in the country started
to operate.
</P>
<P>
She said that during the period, ten companies were involved
in accidents, three planes crashed because of poor weather, four
companies were given warnings and three pilots had their licenses
suspended. 
</P>
</TEXT>
