<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier, U.S. President Have Working Luncheon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The exchange of visits between the
Chinese and U.S. heads of state "will push the ties between the
two countries to enter into a new phase of development," said
Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji here today.
</P>
<P>
During a working luncheon he gave for the visiting U.S.
President Bill Clinton at the Diaoyutai State Guest-house, Zhu
said: "you (Clinton) came to China on a state visit after
President Jiang's U.S. trip last year, thus realizing the exchange
of visits between the heads of state of China and the United
States."
</P>
<P>
"This embodies the common aspiration of the people of China and
the United States, and will push the ties between the two
countries to enter into a new phase of development," Zhu added.
</P>
<P>
Zhu and Clinton exchanged views on the Sino-U.S. relations, and
international and regional issues of common concern, especially
the issue of the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also briefed the U.S. president on China's economic
development and measures taken by the Chinese Government to
further the reform and opening up.
</P>
<P>
Among those attending the working luncheon were Chinese State
Councillor Wu Yi, leading officials of relevant departments and
commissions under the State Council, and principal members of
Clinton's official delegation.  
