<HEADLINE> Zamorano Confident Facing Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Chilean striker Ivan Zamorano said the
whole team were confident for their clash against Brazil in the second
round on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"We're confident for our match Saturday. We have won the chance to
play here against Brazil, and we have to make the most of it," he said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
He said he had a good relationship with Brazil's star striker
Ronaldo, who will be one of the major threats to the Chilean goal
later Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"Of course I know Ronaldo since he plays for my club (Inter Milan).
When he's having a good day, he creates a lot of problems for us,"
said Zamorano.
</P>
<P>
He said it was apparent that Ronaldo played better than him.
</P>
<P>
"Is Ronaldo better than me? I don't doubt it for a minute," he
said. "I'm 31 and have accomplished much in my career, but he still
has his entire life ahead of him."
</P>
<P>
"I get on very well with Ronaldo in Milan, but I think I get on
better with (Marcelo) Salas on the Chilean team," he added.
</P>
<P>
"For now, I can thank God for giving me a chance to play with the
two best strikers in the world: Ronaldo in Milan and Salas on the
Chilean side"
</P>
<P>
He said he would stay with Inter Milan next year but was proud that
Paris Saint-German had an interest in him.
</P>
<P>
"Maybe I'll play in Paris one day," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
