<HEADLINE> Intangible Resources to be Auctioned at International Air Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, June 27 (Xinhua) -- An auction of intangible resources
will be held during the 98 China International Air Show scheduled
for this autumn in Zhuhai.
</P>
<P>
Starting from the autumn of 1996, the exposition has already
become a major annual event for displaying the strength of the
aircraft and space industries of China and the world.
</P>
<P>
According to sources, the tangible resources to be auctioned at
the air show will include the rights to name five major activities
of the air show, and the licences for using over 100 products
specially designed for the event.
</P>
<P>
To date, over 600 Chinese and overseas companies have applied
for participation. The event will be covered by 15 Chinese and
foreign television stations and over 300 media
organizations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
