<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yangtze River Facilitates Operation of Foreign Ships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The Yangtze River, the longest in
China, will introduce an internationally-recognized "sectional
ship piloting system" to facilitate the operation of foreign ships.
</P>
<P>
Also as part of the effort, the ban on night sailing of foreign
ships will be gradually relaxed, according to the river
administrative authorities.
</P>
<P>
According to relevant Chinese legislation, foreign ships
sailing on the Yangtze should be led by Chinese pilots. The river
opened to foreign ships in April, 1983.
</P>
<P>
"Sectional piloting", already in practice on the Mississippi,
the Rhine, the Suez and Panama canals, is designed to enable the
relay of pilots and the non-stopping sailing of the ships on long
journeys.
</P>
<P>
It is highly necessary to implement "sectional piloting" on the
Yangtze, since as long as 1,331 kilometers of the river have
opened to foreign ships, the river authorities said.
</P>
<P>
To facilitate the implementation of the practice, several
piloting relay bases are being built on the Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
Since May, 1983 when the first foreign ship entered the
Yangtze, 77,000 ships from 60 countries and regions of the world
have been using the river course.
</P>
<P>
In order to facilitate piloting, piloting stations have been
built at major ports in Nanjing, Nantong, Zhangjiagang, Zhenjiang,
Shanghai, Wuhan, Jiujiang and Wuhu.
</P>
<P>
There are now 160 pilots working on the river for foreign
ships, who account for one fifth of China's river piloting
force. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980627.0183 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Psychological Consultation Starts Strong in Chinese Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Yang Min's dream to have a
personal psychiatrist has come true since he has joined a private
psychological consultation agency in the Chinese capital of
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Established two months ago as the first privately-owned
psychological body, the Bonian Yangguang (sunshine) Family Health
Advisory Club means the appearance of private psychological
services in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
Yang, in his forties, said that social reforms sped up social
development, meanwhile they also put a bigger mental pressure on
people. "Psychological adjustment is the best thing to do,
whatever difficulties one might meet," Yang added.
</P>
<P>
Yan Jun from the club disclosed that more than 2,000 people
have joined his club, in line with a development momentum to have
personal psychiatrists as people are paying much attention to
psychological health.
</P>
<P>
Many of the members of the club are middle-aged and young
people who usually get help from psychiatrists through
telephones. If necessary, people can also have face-to-face
dialogues with doctors at the clinic.
</P>
<P>
The club provides consultation on personal love affairs,
marriage, education of children, career development and relations
with other people.
</P>
<P>
A survey disclosed that at present some 70 percent of the local
residents are interested in psychological services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
