<HEADLINE> Sino-Tanzanian Military Cooperation Develops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 27 (Xinhua) - A senior officer of the
Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA) said here Saturday that
the friendly cooperation between China and Tanzania in the
military field has contributed much to bilateral relations over
the past years.
</P>
<P>
Major General Sun Qixiang said that the cooperation has
yielded many positive results especially in the training of
military personnel. Sun headed a Chinese delegation of nine
senior officers who have concluded a six-day visit to Tanzania
and left for Zambia and Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
Sun said that during the visit, he held talks with Tanzanian
Defense Minister Edgar Majogo, Chief of the Tanzanian People's
Defense Forces (TPDF) General Robert Mboma, TPDF Chief of Staff
Lt. General Gideon Sayore and other senior officers.
</P>
<P>
"We also visited several military academies and institutes as
well as the Naval and Air bases and exchanged views on military
training with our counterparts," he said.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, consisting of presidents of the PLA military
academies and institutes of the three services, was seen off at
the Dar es Salaam International Airport by Tanzanian senior army
commanders and Zhang Hongxi, Chinese Ambassador to Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Last Sunday when the delegation arrived, a TPDF statement said
that the long-term friendly relationship between China and
Tanzania has developed smoothly in the military field and the
role played by China in assistance to the TPDF has also grown
enormously.  
</P>
