<HEADLINE> Norway Grants Zimbabwe $3M for Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Norway has decided to grant three
million U.S. Dollars to the Zimbabwean Scientific and Industrial
Research and Development Center (SIRDC) for research purposes,
the Zimbabwe News Agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 51.6 million Zimbabwean Dollars, to be provided through
the Norwegian Development Agency, will go into the search for
cost-effective industrial production methods and technologies to
assist local companies to produce quality products.
</P>
<P>
Under an agreement signed Friday in Harare by the two
countries, the Norwegian agency would also facilitate for a
strategic link-up between the SIRDC, the Norwegian Foundation of
Scientific and Industrial Research, other relevant consultants
and scientists at Norwegian universities under a joint pilot
program.
</P>
<P>
The program would be aimed at assisting particularly local
small- and medium-size enterprises with the identification,
sourcing installation and use of technologies to replace the
outdated machinery which most of them still used. 
</P>
