<HEADLINE> NBA Star Barkley Fined in Bar Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- NBA Houston Rochets' star
Charles Barkley was fined Friday and had to make community service
visits to two children's programs to settle charges for throwing a
bar patron through a window last October.
</P>
<P>
"I had allowed myself to be provoked by a malicious bar patron,
and I realize in hindsight that I compounded the problem by not
being initially more cooperative with the officers present,"
Barkley wrote to the judge.
</P>
<P>
Barkley was ordered to pay 320 U.S. dollars in fines and court
costs, and the 34-year-old has to visit a hospital for children
and women and a village as part of his punishment.
</P>
<P>
Barkley lost his temper when Jorge Lugo threw a glass of ice at
a table Barkley was sharing with three women in a bar in Orlando.
</P>
<P>
Barkley chased the bar patron and picked him up and threw him
through a window. 
</P>
