<HEADLINE> Brazil Sees Growth in Exports to Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's exports to African
countries rose to 585 million U.S. dollars in the first five
months this year, up 18.6 percent from the year-ago level, press
reports said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria, Morocco and Egypt are reported to be the main
importers of Brazilian goods, with their purchases up by 72.9,
74.4, and 43.3 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
In the same period, Brazil's imports from Africa also
increased, with Africa's share in the Brazilian imports going up
to 37 percent from 28 percent in the first five months last year.
</P>
