<DOCNO> XIE19980627.0235 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Reduce Oil Production Starting July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government has
decided to reduce oil production by 30,000 barrels per day (bpd)
to 1.28 million bpd starting next month, local press Saturday
quoted a minister as saying.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia will produce only 1.28 million bpd for one year
starting July 1, down from 1.38 million bpd as targeted for that
period, Minister for Mines and Energy Kuntoro Mangkusobroto said.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made in support of the agreement reached by
the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) that each
member, except Iraq, is to reduce production to anticipate an
oversupply in the world market.
</P>
<P>
The ministerial conference in Vienna last week decided to
reduce the organization's total oil production by 600,000 to
800,000 bpd.
</P>
<P>
The total OPEC production (excluding Iraq) on July 1, 1998 to
June 30, 1999 was put at 24.397 million bpd, down from 26.987
million bpd.
</P>
<P>
"The decisions made by OPEC and non-OPEC countries slightly
boosted the oil price. The price however has decreased to 10.11
U.S. dollars per barrel since June 15 as world demand for oil in
the second quarter of 1998 dwindled," the ministry's spokesman
Budi Sulistyo was quoted as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
