<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Advance Women's Cause </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar is planning to step up its
scheme to advance the women's cause phase by phase for the
progress of the nation based on patriotism.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a meeting of the Myanmar National Committee for
Women's Affairs (MNCWA) here Friday, Lieutenant General Khin Nyunt
urged the committee to render effective assistance down to the
grassroots level for health, education and social progress of
Myanmar women to safeguard the country's tradition, culture, race
and religion, official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Khin Nyunt, who is first secretary of the Myanmar State Peace
and Development Council, also urged the committee to strive for
the emergence of a peaceful, developed and modern nation in
cooperation with government organizations and non-governmental
ones including the Myanmar Maternal and Child Welfare
Association.
</P>
<P>
He also called on the committee to strive to implement programs
worked out in line with the tasks laid down by the Beijing
Declaration adopted at the United Nations Fourth World Conference
on Women held in Beijing in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The MNCWA was formed after Myanmar had agreed to the Beijing
Declaration.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a workshop of the MNCWA on women's development took
place here last month to draw up the programs and plans for
implementing the country's women development projects including
education, health and socio-economic development as well as
protection of Myanmar women against violence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
