<HEADLINE> Brazil Sees Drop in Exports to Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's exports to Asian
countries in the first five months this year dropped by more than
16 percent from the year-ago level to 2.37 billion U.S. dollars,
press reports said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Sales to Japan -- Brazil's top Asian customer -- fell 19
percent while the Asian market as a whole accounted for 11.3
percent of the Brazilian exports, compared with 14.2 percent in
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
However, the South American country registered growth in its
exports to the mainland of China, China's Hong Kong and Taiwan,
with rates of 8.5 percent, 4.2 percent and 51.4 percent,
respectively. 
</P>
