<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hunchbacked People Made Upright Without Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-seven year-old Yang Mingjian
has his hunchback stretched upright only after four weeks of
no-surgery treatment in a rehabilitation hospital in Northeast
China's Heilongjiang province.
</P>
<P>
He is among 285 hunchbacked people who became taller after one
to four weeks treatment at the Heilongjiang Rehabilitation
Hospital, doctors of the hospital claimed.
</P>
<P>
They said they achieved a total effective rate of 95 percent
and a patient is 11 centimeters taller than before treatment.
</P>
<P>
They said after years research, they developed a unique
non-surgery method for the treatment of the hunchbacked.
</P>
<P>
The patients are treated on pneumatic-electric traction beds
for a period together with the application of the traditional
Chinese bonesetting technique.
</P>
<P>
Doctors said the treatment is specially effective for those
contracted with ankylosing spondylitis, central rheumatoid
arthritis and senile retrograde spinal osteoarthritis.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
