<DOCNO> XIE19980627.0251 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Girl with Rare Heart Undergoes Correction Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 27 (Xinhua) -- A hospital in northwest China's
Shaanxi province has successfully made a correction operation for
a "three-atrium-heart" girl. The surgery ended her 11 years heart
disorder.
</P>
<P>
An ordinary people's heart has only a left atrium and a right
atrium. However, the 11-year-old girl has three. Her left atrium
was divided into two parts with a six millimeter hole on the
central part of the diaphragm.
</P>
<P>
The Shaanxi People's hospital made the three-hour operation for
 widening the hole on the left cucurbit-shaped atriums and
removing the atrial septum between the left and right atriums.
</P>
<P>
Doctors at the Hospital said the girl, coming from north
China's Hebei Province, often had tachycardia and in some cases,
her heart would beat 180 times per minute. She often felt
suppressed in the chest and faint because of blood blocking in her
left atrium.
</P>
<P>
With the operation, she now can live a normal life. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
