and Japan's Norick Abe came third in 2:02.601.
</P>
<P>
Championship leader Alex Criville of Spain was ninth fastest at
2:03.469 and will start from the third line on the grid.
</P>
<P>
Criville leads the championship with 103 points, ahead of
Italian Max Biaggi with 98 and Carlos Checa of Spain with 95
points. Doohan is fourth on 90 points. 
