<HEADLINE> No Wild Card for UEFA Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- European soccer's governing body
(UEFA) decided at its executive committee meeting here that no
club who had failed to qualify for the competition would be
offered a wild card place.
</P>
<P>
UEFA said in a statement the executive committee had examined
and rejected a request for a wild card entry by AC Milan, who were
out of the running for the UEFA Cup after finishing 10th in
Italy's Serie A.
</P>
<P>
A plan had been put forward at a UEFA meeting in Paris earlier
this month to give wild card entries to European champions of the
past five years who had not been able to earn places in any of the
three European club competitions.
</P>
<P>
AC Milan came into the reckoning as champions in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980627.0262 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-27 </DATE_TIME>
