<HEADLINE> Qingdao Residents Study Foreign Languages With Keen Interest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Foreign language studies are
popular with both Chinese and foreign residents in Qingdao, a port
city in east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
A Chinese-English salon established last year has attracted
more than 20,000 Chinese and foreign participants who converse in
the two languages and attend parties.
</P>
<P>
Many participants have made rapid progress in language
aquisition by participating in the many colorful activities.
</P>
<P>
The salon also sponsors English language contests for students
in middle and primary schools during summer and winter holidays,
with related activities attracting the participation of over 800
children and their parents. 
</P>
