<HEADLINE> Philippine President-elect Names Army, Police Chiefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President-elect Joseph
Estrada has named Lt. Gen. Joselin Nazareno chief of staff of the
Armed Forces of the Philippines (AFP) and Chief Supt. Roberto
Lastimoso director-general of the Philippine National Police
(PNP).
</P>
<P>
The official Philippine Journal reported Saturday that Estrada
announced the appointment Friday.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that Nazareno, 55, will replace Gen. Clemente
Mariano as the AFP chief of staff while Lastimoso, 54, will take
over the post to be vacated by PNP Director-general Santiago
Alino.
</P>
<P>
The two new chiefs are graduates of the Philippine Military
Academy, according to the paper.
</P>
<P>
Estrada will be sworn in as president for a single six-year
term next Tuesday to succeed President Fidel Ramos. 
</P>
