<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Former Tennis Queen Graf out of Wimbledon Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Former Wimbledon champion Steffi
Graf of Germany failed to qualify for the women's last-16 stage of
the 1998 Wimbledon tennis championships Friday after losing in
straight sets 6-4, 7-5 to Natasha Zvereva of Belarus.
</P>
<P>
Graf, who was recovering from a 18-month injury, today looked
vulnerable and was unable to find her old-time magic when she
snatched seven Wimbledon titles.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Zvereva, who lost her all 17 matches over the past
ten years to the fomer tennis queen, played aggressively and
totally dominiated the whole match.
</P>
<P>
With tennis genius Mitina Hingis of Switzerland and other
talented young girls in the coming quickly, the once glorious Graf
era is slowing coming to an end.
</P>
<P>
In another third round clash, second seed Lindsay Davenport of
the United States reached the last 16 after beating Maria
Alejandra Vento of Venezuela 6-3, 1-6, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
In the men's events, 6th seed Pat Rafter of Australia became
the first player to qualify for the men's last-16 after
eliminating his Swedish opponent Magus Gustafsson in four-sets
6-3, 6-7, 6-2, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
In a delayed second round encounter, 14th seed Goran Ivansevic
of Croatia defeated Ukrainian veterian player Andrei Medveduv 3-6,
7-6, 6-4, 6-0. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
