<HEADLINE> Turkish President Visits Moldova </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleiman
Demirel Friday ended his two-day official visit to the Republic of
Moldova. Two important agreements concerning the exclusion of
double taxation and the joint production of medicines were signed
during the visit.
</P>
<P>
According to the Moldovan national Moldpres news agency,
President Petre Luchinsky and his Turkish counterpart Demirel
expressed hope that the visit would be a new important moment in
the relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"The relations between Moldova and Turkey are very good,"
stated Luchinsky on Thursday after a tete-a-tete meeting with
Demirel. He added that "there is a striving on both parts for
raising these relations onto a higher level."
</P>
<P>
Demirel said that the Turkish-Moldovan relations and
cooperation possess a great potential.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Demirel also met with Chairman of the
Moldovan Parliament, Dumitru Diacov, and the Premier Ion Ciubuc.
</P>
</TEXT>
