<HEADLINE> Football Hooligan Detained in Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 26 (Xinhua) -- German police have detained a
23-year-old man in Hamburg who is suspected of participating in
beating and fatally injuring a French policeman on the fringes of
a World Cup match in France five days ago.
</P>
<P>
Hamburg police said Friday evening that the man had admitted
that he had been portrayed on a press photo which documented the
violent scene.
</P>
<P>
The 44-year-old French police officer suffered serious head
injures during clashes with German hooligans after the World Cup
game between Germany and Yugoslavia last Sunday in the French city
of Lens.
</P>
<P>
The violent act sent a shock across Germany with Chancellor
Helmut Kohl condemning it as "a shame" for the country.
</P>
<P>
Two other German hooligans have already been arrested by French
police earlier this week in connection with the incident.
</P>
</TEXT>
