<TEXT>
<P>
LENS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Colombia coach Hernan Gomez said England
had the upper hand as his team was out of tournament after their 2-1
loss to England here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"You honestly have to say England were the better side. Quite
simply England and Romania were better than we were, we are still
learning," said Gomez.
</P>
