<BODY>
<HEADLINE> England Coach Hoddle Happy with Win </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LENS, France, June 26 (Xinhua) -- England coach Glenn Hoddle said
he was delighted by the win that sent his team to the second round in
the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
He said, "Overall it was a terrific performance. The lads were very
very positive, the way they were focused in the dressing room and
responded to the challenge, I never really expected any other result.
We're on our way but let's not get carried away."
</P>
<P>
Hoddle said they won because they had a correct tactical direction
in the game.
</P>
<P>
He added, "Tactically we got it right, the passing was just right.
We lost the reins in the second half a bit but the amount of chances
we created, we could have scored four or five."
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the performance of Michael Owen, who started for
England for the first time, Hoddle said: "I told Michael to go out
there and play as free as a bird. He was bit nervous in the first 15
minutes but he was lightning once he got into the game." 
</P>
</TEXT>
