<HEADLINE> Vasily Sova Becomes First Moldovan Ambassador to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Vasily Sova has been appointed
an Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary Ambassador of the Republic of
Moldova to China, the Moldovan INTERLIC news agency reported
Friday quoting a decree of the head of the state, Petre Luchinsky.
</P>
<P>
Vasily Sova is 39 years old and occupied the position of the
deputy Minister of Foreign Affairs before the appointment.
</P>
<P>
China and Moldova established diplomatic relations on January
30, 1992. Moldova was represented till now by Charge d'affaires,
Vladimir Cusnir.  
</P>
