<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romanian President Appeals for Eliminating Drug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Romanian President Emil
Constantinescu Friday called on the young, the education staff and
the civic organizations to join the efforts to eliminate the drug
phenomenon from the life of the future Romania.
</P>
<P>
In a message addressed on the international Day against drug
abuses and drug smuggling, Constantinescu stated that Romania "has
become a place for the transiting and stocking of drugs". Even if
the drug consuming is relatively low, more and more young people
take to the narcotics, he added.
</P>
<P>
The President stressed that the Romanian state has committed
itself to a triple self-defense action, namely to improve the
legislation, restructure the institutions and sustain education
activities in the field. "These directions would be blended into a
national strategy to fight against drug trafficking and
consuming," he said.
</P>
<P>
Romania is part of the United Nations' Convention and signatory
of programs and resolutions made by the U.N, which are meant to
develop international cooperation in combating drug smuggling and
consuming, Constantinescu said.
</P>
<P>
He said that in 1998 Bucharest would host the regional
Conference for the fight against drug smuggling and consuming.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
