<HEADLINE> Tunisian Coach Says Romania Deserve the Draw </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SAINT-DENIS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Tunisian coach Ali Selmi said
Romania deserved their point after the two teams fought to a 1-1
draw here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"The first half was the best we have played in the competition.
In the second they were stronger and much better organised and
they deserved the draw."
</P>
<P>
Selmi, who replaced sacked Henryk Kasperczak, said:"After the
first game when we didn't play well and the second when we had
chances and didn't score it was very hard to motivate the players for
another game where there no real incentives."
</P>
<P>
Romanian coach Anghel Iordanescu was apparently relieved after
his team salvaged the draw and qualified as the group winners:"We
were very poor in the first half and our whole game was
disorganised," said Iordanescu, "In the second half we played much
more like our normal game."
</P>
<P>
"It is clear that the lack of organisation was my fault as I had
changed five players." Iordanescu said.
</P>
<P>
Viorel Moldovan, who scored the equaliser for Romania, said:"I'm
very proud of what I did but I wasn't the only one. The whole team
won, we were better in the second half." 
</P>
</TEXT>
