<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Scifo Retires After Team's Elimination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Belgian veteran midfielder Enco Scifo
announced on Friday his retirement from international soccer.
</P>
<P>
Scifo, 32, has just played his fourth World Cup finals. He said
his 84th cap for Belgium against South Korea on Thursday would be
his last international appearence.
</P>
<P>
Belgium were forced to a 1-1 draw by the South Koreans and that
cast them a place in the second round.
</P>
<P>
"I would have liked to continue my international career. But in
these conditions it is no longer possible," Scifo said, "I don't
feel I am important to the squad. So for me it is over."
</P>
<P>
It was Scifo's second retirement announcement this year. In
February he said he had quit international soccer when he was left out
of the squad for a World Cup warm-up against the United States.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
