<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japanese Coach Quit after Losing to Jamaica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LYON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Japanese coach Takeshi Okada resigned
on Friday after his team suffered their third one-goal defeat at the
World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Japan lost to Jamaica 2-1 on Friday. They were defeated 1-0
by Argentina and Croatia respectively.
</P>
<P>
"I will quit as a professional coach. When a coach fails to
achieve what he set outs to do, he should quit." said Okada.
</P>
<P>
Okada said:"It is my responsibility. I was not able to draw the
best out of the players in this match."
</P>
<P>
"Today the team was much too slow in attacking the Jamaican goal
and made too many needless passes, even though they put 100 percent
effort into it." said Okada.
</P>
<P>
Jamaicai coach Rene Simoes said Okada had nothing to be ashamed
of:"I think japan should feel very proud as well. They played three
wonderful games." 
</P>
