<HEADLINE> England Enter Second Round in World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LENS, France, June 26 (Xinhua) -- England reached the second round
in the World Cup finals after beating Colombia 2-0 in their last group
G match here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
England finished second in the group behind Romania, who tied with
Tunisia 1-1 in the new Stade de France in St-Denis in the other match
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Tottenham Hotspur midfielder Darren Anderton opened the scoring for
England in the 21st minute by shotting the ball in small angle over
Colombian keeper Farid Mondragon off the near post.
</P>
<P>
Manchester United playmaker David Beckham made it 2-0 for England
in the 30th minute, when he blasted a booming 25-meter free kick into
the upper left corner of the net.
</P>
<P>
The free kick was awarded when Paul Ince was fouled out of the
penalty area.
</P>
<P>
Paul Scholes had an early chance in the second minute but the
long-range shot went straight to Mondragon.
</P>
<P>
Scholes, who plays for Manchester United, appeared extremely
dangerous before the Colombian goal when he shot twice in the first
four minutes of the second half.
</P>
<P>
Beckham also had later opportunities, including one in the 83rd
minute when he lobbed a shot high over the bar.
</P>
<P>
Liverpool teenager Michael Owen squandered a chance in the second
half when he shot the ball right into the arms of Mondragon in a
one-on-one occassion.
</P>
<P>
The match was largely dominated by the Englishmen and the best
Colombian chance came in the 79th minute but Hamilton Ricard blasted
wide off the goal.
</P>
<P>
England will meet Argentina while Romania face Croatia in the
second round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
