<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania Qualify as Group G Winners with 1-1 Draw </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SAINT-DENIS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Romania qualified as Group G
winners after drawing with Tunisia 1-1 here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian team, which need a draw to win the top position of
the Group, were stunned by an early goal at the 10th minute when
referee awarded a penalty to the Tunisian team. Skander Souayah
made no mistake on the spot.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian team fought hard but didn't get the equaliser until
the 72nd minute. Adrian Ilie beat a off-side trap and centered past
the Tunisian goal-keeper while substitute Viorel Moldovan fired the
ball into net at the first time.
</P>
<P>
With the draw, the Romanian team qualified as group winners with
7 points. England, which beat Colombia 2-0 in an exciting game,
finished runners-up with 6 points.
</P>
<P>
Romania will take on Croatia while England play Argentina in the
round of 16. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
